The paper deals with content-based image retrieval (CBIR) using deep learning features, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of pre-trained network models from deep learning convolution networks also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) techniques. Additionally, the paper proposes a pre-clustering method, which involves clustering algorithms and optimization techniques, falling under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
